summary:
The Security Council,

Adopting resolution 2054 (2012) at its 6794th meeting on 29 June 2012,

Noting the International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda's (ICTR) Completion Strategy Report and the updated trial and appeals schedule,

Recalling resolutions 955 (1994), 1503 (2003), 1534 (2004), and 1966 (2010) concerning the ICTR and the International Residual Mechanism for Criminal Tribunals (Mechanism),

Decides:

1. To allow Judges William H. Sekule, Solomy Balungi Bossa, and Mparany Mamy Richard Rajohnson to continue serving until 31 December 2012 or the completion of the Ngirabatware case;
2. To extend Judge Vagn Joensen's term of office until 31 December 2014 to complete the Tribunal's work;
3. To request the ICTR to report on the projected schedule for the transition of functions to the Mechanism, with concrete estimated dates, to complete all remaining work by 31 December 2014;
4. To stress the importance of adequate staffing for the ICTR to complete its work expeditiously and calls for cooperation to address staffing issues;
5. To urge States to intensify cooperation and render assistance to the ICTR, particularly in the arrest and surrender of remaining fugitives;
6. To commend States that have accepted the relocation of acquitted or convicted persons and calls on other States to cooperate in this regard;

Decides to remain seized of the matter.
